{
  "name": "layer 2",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Analyze this sensor anomaly event for machine {{ $json.body.machine_id }}:\nTime stamp: {{ $json.body.timestamp }}\n\nMachine ID: {{ $json.body.machine_id }}\ncomplete json: {{ JSON.stringify($json.body) }}\nTimestamp: {{ $json.body.timestamp }}\n\nProvide analysis in the following JSON format:\n{\n  \"current_situation\": \"text description\",\n  \"risk_score\": \"number(0-100)\",\n  \"alert\": [true/false, \"context for alert\"],\n  \"schMain\": [true/false, \"timings for scheduling maintenance\"]\n}\n\nDo not include any extra text outside the JSON.\nTo calculate the risk score:\nThe Risk Score  is  calculated on a scale of 0 to 100.\n1. The Base Intensity (The Starting Point)\nThe calculation begins by looking at the \"Distance from Normal.\"\n\nThe Logic: We take the sensor that has deviated the most from its average behavior (the highest Z-score).\n\nThe Weight: We convert that statistical distance into a 0–100 scale. If a sensor is three times more volatile than usual, it starts with a base risk of 30.\n\n2. The Multivariate Multiplier (The \"Physics\" Check)\nWe then look at how many different sensors are failing at the same time on that specific machine.\n\nThe Logic: If only one sensor is high, the risk stays low because it could be a sensor glitch.\n\nThe Weight: If two or more related sensors (like Vibration and Temperature) are both high, we add a \"Correlation Bonus\" of 20 to 30 points. This is because multiple symptoms confirm a physical reality.",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are the Fleet Supervisor orchestrator for a predictive maintenance system. Your role is to coordinate analysis of sensor anomalies and determine appropriate action. You only reply in the following JSON format: {\"current_situation\":\"text\", \"risk_score\":\"text\", \"alert\":[true/false, \"text\"], \"schMain\":[true/false, \"text\"]}"
        }
      },
      "id": "37bc49db-9fee-4bcc-a9c3-5612163a5df0",
      "name": "Fleet Supervisor",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        368,
        -288
      ]
